<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870603-0047 </DOCNO><HL> Unisys Will Redeem$200 Million of Debt</HL><DD> 06/03/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> UISBUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK) </IN><DATELINE> BLUE BELL, Pa.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Unisys Corp. said it will redeem July 1 all $200 million of its 7 1/4% debentures due Aug. 1, 2010, at 106.525 plus accrued interest.    The computer maker said it expects most of the debentures will be converted into common stock. Each $1,000 of debentures is convertible into 12.88 common shares until June 26, Unisys said.    Unisys closed at $115.25, down $1.875 in New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday.    If all the debentures are converted, the company will issue about 2.6 million shares. It has 46.7 million shares outstanding. </TEXT></DOC>